---
title: Next.js
name: Next.js
description: Send email from a Next.js Server Action with the top-level mail().
category: Frameworks
---

Postboi is framework-agnostic â€” read the request's `FormData` in a Server Action and hand it
straight to [`mail()`](/api). Postboi extracts the [special fields](/formdata#special-fields)
and renders the rest into a tidy HTML table.

```tsx
// app/page.tsx
import { mail } from 'postboi';

async function submit(formData: FormData) {
	'use server';

	// Reply-to comes from the submitted email, so replying reaches the sender.
	formData.set('_reply_to', String(formData.get('contactâ†’email') ?? ''));
	formData.set('_subject', 'Contact Form');

	await mail({ body: formData });
}

export default function Page() {
	return (
		<form action={submit}>
			<input name="contactâ†’name" placeholder="Name" required />
			<input name="contactâ†’email" type="email" placeholder="Email" required />
			<textarea name="detailsâ†’message" placeholder="Message" />
			<button type="submit">Send</button>
		</form>
	);
}
```

Field names use the [`fieldsetâ†’field`](/formdata#grouped-fields) syntax. The provider and
default recipient come from [`postboi.config.ts`](/config) â€” a `POSTBOI_TOKEN` routes to
[Postboi Cloud](/cloud), or pick any [provider](/providers).

**Runnable example:** [`examples/nextjs-provider-postboi`](https://github.com/darbymanning/postboi/tree/main/examples/nextjs-provider-postboi).
